<p><b>Gerald Vincent Bull</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1928-03-09"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-09"><a href="/wiki/March_9" title="March 9">March 9</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1928" title="1928">1928</a></span> - <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1990-03-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-22"><a href="/wiki/March_22" title="March 22">March 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1990" title="1990">1990</a></span>) was a Canadian engineer who developed long range <a href="/wiki/Artillery" title="Artillery">artillery</a>. He moved from project to project in his quest to economically launch a <a href="/wiki/Satellite" title="Satellite">satellite</a> using a huge artillery piece. To this end he designed the <a href="/wiki/Project_Babylon" title="Project Babylon">Project Babylon</a> "<a href="/wiki/Supergun" title="Supergun">supergun</a>" for the <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraqi</a> government. He was assassinated by a gunman outside his home in <a href="/wiki/Brussels" title="Brussels">Brussels</a>, <a href="/wiki/Belgium" title="Belgium">Belgium</a>.</p>
